[[File:Tarbiyat_library.jpg|thumb|right]] '''Tarbiat library''' ({{lang-fa|کتابخانه تربیت}}) is the first state library in Iran, established in 1921 at [[Tabriz]]. The library was founded by [[Mahammad Ali Tarbiat]], Iranian journalist and politician as "Ma'aref public library and reading room" ({{lang-fa|كتابخانه و قرائتخانه عمومي معارف}}) which was later renamed after its founder to Tarbiat library. <ref>{{cite encyclopedia |last= Azadeh |first= Fridun |encyclopedia=دایرة‌المعارف کتابداری و اطلاع‌رسانی |title=کتابخانه عمومی تربیت تبریز |trans-title=Tabriz Tarbiat public library |url=http://portal.nlai.ir/daka/Wiki%20Pages/%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87%20%D8%B9%D9%85%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8A%20%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%AA%20%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B2.aspx |accessdate= 3 Dec 2012 |language= Persian |date= 5 Dec 2007 |publisher= سازمان اسناد و کتابخانه ملی جمهوری اسلامی ایران |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/67S9XKuMS |archivedate= 6 May 2012 }}</ref>
